OL,6,F"They were simply doing their job, and
OL,7,Fmade countless attempts to communicate
OL,8,Fwith Sarfaraz about their intentions
OL,9,Fon the visit and why they were there.
OL,11,F"Despite several warnings, he has
OL,12,Fdangerously thrown hot oil at them in
OL,13,Fa bid to get away from them ` and went
OL,14,Fon to deny his violent behaviour
OL,15,Fdespite overwhelming evidence against
OL,16,Fhim.
OL,18,F"Sarfaraz even defended his actions in
OL,19,Finterview, claiming he was preparing
OL,20,Fto cook an egg while officers attended
OL,21,Fthe house."
